review:

It's super cute, but it's also super pointy and it made a little painful raw cut on my nose. Piercing was done in 2007, so it's not new. I even loosened it so it's not constantly touching my skin and it doesn't matter, it still rubs.

product: Double Nose Ring Hoop for Single Piercing, 14k Gold Filled or Sterling Silver Spiral Twist Nose Hoop for Women Men
review:
I tried a few sizes of this nose ring before finding the right diameter and thickness I wanted. The previous one I had from another company was 7mm / 20g - so I ordered a 7mm / 20g from this company and it was a bigger hoop than the 7mm from the other company. I then ordered a 6mm / 20g & 6mm / 22g (in case I wanted a thinner one).

Ended up using the 6mm / 20g and it fits PERFECT. Sits close to the nose. I did order a right side one for my left side piercing per instruction / other comments. It's kind of hard to put in the first time and VERY hard to remove - but if you watch the video it really helps.

I absolutely love it and suggest it to anyone looking for a double hoop!

product: Double Nose Ring Hoop for Single Piercing, 14k Gold Filled or Sterling Silver Spiral Twist Nose Hoop for Women Men
review:
I love this nose ring. Definately find a way to measure your nose to determine which size you need before ordering. I started with the 6mm (ordered on accident) and 3 days later went up to 7mm when my nose started to tear. I wound up reordering (now have spent $30 trying to find the right size) and I went to 9mm which is a little big for ly liking and I am thinking of reordering a 8mm.
It comes nearly packsged with a cleaning cloth to use if it begins to tarnish and the silver is definately silver, I have had no adverse reaction to the metal and there had been no tarnishing so far.
As far as difficulty putting the ring in, you gently pull the ring apart and sort of screw it into your piercing and twist it around yo get it to fit properly. To me, the most difficult part is taking it out.
I definately recommend this ring and any problems with my piercing were the result of not enough knowledge of what the appropriate size for my nostril should be and I will hopefully be reordering in a size 8mm soon

review: The name plate, beads, and rings are 5 stars plus. The mail packaging with a personalized sticker and lanyard bag is such great marketing. There was some problems I should have noticed from the photos, because it wasn't like they were hiding it and some were just unique to my order maybe. One as another reviewer mentioned, the paracord is as thin as 4 ply yarn which makes it a little uncomfortable on your bare neck if you add any weight to it like keys, whistle, or etcetera. Second when I tried to test yank the clasp to see if it was breakaway for any special education student who might yank it, it did not break away on my neck and again was uncomfortable. I took it off my neck and tried to pull it apart with all my strength and it wouldn't separate. I tried to twist it apart and the clasp still didn't break away. I got to admit that paracord and clasp is strong, because all that full strength yanking on that paracord and clasp and neither snapped or broke. Another small thing was the tassle was broke in the package, but that can be super glued back in. I am keeping it and just wearing it with a second lanyard, as I am genuinely impressed except for the paracord and clasp which like I said I should have noticed in the pictures. So if you are not holding a lot or not in special education definitely get this!
